main event: Unidentified flying object sighted near Baker, Oregon on October 10, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as elliptical in shape, approximately 50 feet in diameter, and emitting a bright, reddish-orange glow.
The object was observed for approximately 3 minutes before disappearing from view.
A sketch of the object was provided, but no photographs could be obtained.
The case is classified as 'UNIDENTIFIED' pending further investigation.
Multiple observers, including civilians and military personnel, reported seeing the object in the sky.
sighted object: elliptical-shaped object with a bright, reddish-orange glow
photographs: no, but a sketch was provided
